yay
however
when i emailed iobridge yesterday to sort out the range we should use
they just emailed our client and said why is uncorked contacting us
really great customer service.
they are being so ridiculous
i was just reading that email karen
GIVE US THE RANGE.
apparently the way the tank guy hooked them up, the API output doesn't map linearly to tank percentages
<http://blog-imgs-33.fc2blog.us/f/u/y/fuyushin/200908151435009d0.jpg>
which is fine, but they're trying to say that the function it creates is not worth figuring out, so just estimate it
but getting precise readings of how much beer is in each tank is _the only thing that makes these smart tanks worth using_
"To avoid having to work out the governing equation, I was hoping that we could just figure out some ballpark ranges for what 0,25,50 and 100 percent were."
"I'm not actually sure how the sensor works, so I can't say for sure."
What?
ioBridge is basically saying "We don't know what the tank readings we're giving you mean, so let's just guess!!"
and the client wrote me an email this morning saying it sounds like our only option is guess.
and i'm like no.
We should suggest this design change
nice
we'll remove the i guess when they figure out how the sensors work.
I like that.
<@U02613K0X>:  i need to respond to the client
is it easier to meet & get your thoughts on iobridge's email

or with work on your plate, discuss via email? i'm trying to find a way forward that doesn't involve us doing trial & error. so maybe understanding a) would a range like 50% equals 170-199 (making this up) work, or are we still missing information/need SOMEBODY to know how the sensors work?
<@U026AP8CM> could you come to walnut table please?
<@U02618EV1> lol
